data.description: This inviting traditional-style home is tucked away on a quiet street in Carriage Lane. You'll notice great curb-appeal with attractive landscaping and a full lawn irrigation system in both the front yard and backyard. The roof was newly installed in March 2023. The attached two-car garage gives you plenty of space for parking and storage. As you enter, you're greeted by new luxury vinyl plank floors, soaring cathedral ceilings, and a spacious open floor plan with a great flow for entertaining and everyday living. You'll also find ample storage space with many closets throughout the home. The formal dining room will be perfect for dinners with family and friends. Enjoy cool evenings in front of the cozy fireplace in the family room.The kitchen offers stainless steel appliances, plenty of cabinet and counter space, a pantry for additional storage space, and a breakfast/casual dining area overlooking the backyard. The spacious first-floor master bedroom features a tray ceiling, a walk-in closet, and a private en suite bathroom with a dual vanity, a jetted garden tub, and a separate shower. The rest of the bedrooms are located upstairs where you'll also find new carpet. The bonus room over the garage could be used as a 4th bedroom or it would also make an excellent game room, entertainment room, children's play room, or home office. The patio and large privacy-fenced backyard will be perfect for grilling out, entertaining, or watching the kids and/or pets play. Conveniently located near shopping, dining, the interstate, Nexton, and Historic Downtown Summerville. Come see your new home, today!
